where Etarget is the real-time PCR efficiency of a target gene transcript (90%–110%); Eref is the real-time PCR efficiency of the reference gene transcript; cycle threshold (Ct) is the number of cycles required for the fluorescent signal to cross the threshold; ΔCttarget is the Ct deviation of the control – sample for the target gene transcript; and ΔCtref = Ct deviation of control – sample for the reference gene transcript.
